Subject: Re: [T2] Should caliper bleed screw leak?

On Thu, 9 Jun 2005, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> That sounds fine.  I doubt the threads are worn out because most likely
> they haven't been turned more than a few times in the lifetime of the bus.

> Plus, when you open it, you only open it enough to let the fluid out.
> Whether it comes out through the threads or through the nipple, it
> doesn't really matter - the fluid's coming out and that's what you want.
>   You just want to make dang sure that there is no fluid coming out
> while it's tight!!

The problem is that he is pressure-bleeding from the wheel end!  For
conventional "pump the pedal" bleeding the threads seal fine, but if
you're putting pressure on the system from the bleeder end the pressure
will push fluid past the threads.

George
